[Maps of Kenya: https://goo.gl/pcUuf4 and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5658608,174. Trans-Nzoia county is a county in the former Rift Valley Province, Kenya, located between the Nzoia River and Mount Elgon 380 km (236 mi) northwest of Nairobi. At its centre is the town of Kitale, which is the capital and largest town. It can be found on a map at https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans-Nzoia_County. - Mod.LL]

